//GIAANNpy Specification (prompts):

---
v2a (Codex IDE GPT-5.4->GPT-5.5) [under development]:
- add proto GIAANNproto2a1a - start option useModalityOR=True:
	- GIAANNor_datasets.py: add huggingface datasetType for video (find an appropriate dataset for short approx 1-3 minute lengthed, moderate resolution, video streams).
	- GIAANNor_RFfilters.py: initialise a set of receptive field (RF) filters:
		- it is recommended you both a) reuse and b) implement from scratch a GPU accelerated library for generating and applying natural RFs based on option modalityORuseExternalRFfilterLibrary:
			- any RF filter code should be added to new file GIAANNor_RFfilters.py.
			- the natural RF filters can be a combination of ellipsoidal and gabor filters.
			- RF filter creation examples:
				- see ATORpt_RF (https://github.com/bairesearch/ATORpt) for creating a variety of natural contrastive ellipsoidal filters.
				- see SANIORpt (https://github.com/bairesearch/SANIORpt) dev/SANI-2DObjectRecognitionArchitectureDevelopment-20August2022a.pdf coloured low level ellipsoidal filters.
		- these RF filters will be independently applied to each token in each layer, and will take the most activated filter for any given sequence iteration (train snapshot).
		- for this initial implementation, the RFs will only be applied to layer l=0 (do not apply RFs to higher layers).
	- GIAANNor_main.py:processSequenceTemplate() for each video stream (sequence):
		- GIAANNor_datasets.py: sample the video into a series of sequence snapshots using modalityORframesPerSnapshot (do not apply any averaging, just skip frames as necessary).
		- GIAANNor_tokens.py: tokenise each snapshot into a series of columns using modalityORpixelsPerColumn (executed in parallel using pytorch):
			- each column in modalityName=="OR" represents a particular a) x token and b) y token in the snapshot (forming a 2D map like the visual cortex V1), and c) a particular layer l in the substrate (forming a hierarchical visual cortex).
			- for this initial implementation, only train layer l=0 (do not train the higher layers).
		- GIAANNor_RFfilters.py: for each token in the snapshot (executed in parallel using pytorch):
			- apply the RF filters to the token (executed in parallel using pytorch):
				- apply a threshold and take the a) most activated filter in the column, and b) only if it is above modalityORRFfilterThreshold.
				- this selects a feature for the column in the layer (if any were selected).
				- each layer column has a maximum of 1 feature trained for every iteration in a sequence.
				- note in the modalityName=="NLP" implementation, only 1 feature of 1 column is trained for every iteration in a sequence (modalityName=="OR" is different in that multiple columns can be simulataneously activated by a snapshot).
				- if no RF filters are active in a column for a given snapshot, that column is not trained.
			- use a predefined function to convert the RFfilter index selected into an ASCII textual code (this becomes the feature "word" and "lemma" used by GIAANN).
		- GIAANNor_sequenceConcepts.py:
			- create a new function to generate the sequence data in the correct format expected by GIAANNcmn_databaseNetworkTrain.
				- see for example processSequenceTemplate(): "GIAANNnlp_sequenceConcepts.detectNewFeatures(databaseNetworkObject, tokens, allowNewFeatures)".
		- GIAANNcmn_sequenceObservedColumns.py (or GIAANNor_sequenceObservedColumns.py): generate sequenceObservedColumns object for modalityName=="OR":
			- see for example processSequenceTemplate(): "sequenceObservedColumns = GIAANNcmn_sequenceObservedColumns.SequenceObservedColumns()".
			- ensure that class GIAANNcmn_sequenceObservedColumns.py:SequenceObservedColumns can be easily upgraded to support modalityName=="OR" (not just modalityName=="NLP"):
				- if not create new file GIAANNor_sequenceObservedColumns.py, and move GIAANNcmn_sequenceObservedColumns.py NLP specific code to new file GIAANNnlp_sequenceObservedColumns.py.
		- GIAANNcmn_databaseNetworkTrain.py: execute the existing train code on the entire sequence of snapshots (selected column features):
			- see for example processSequenceTemplate(): "GIAANNcmn_prediction.processConceptWordsInference()" and "trained = GIAANNcmn_databaseNetworkTrain.trainConceptWords()".
			- the existing GIAANNcmn_databaseNetworkTrain.py code should support multiple columns features being simultaneously active per time step in the trained sequence (even though this is not used by modalityName=="NLP").
		 		- if it does not, split the relevant incompatible sections of train code based on modalityName=="OR"/"NLP".
	Implementation notes:
		- ensure all GIAANNproto2a1a upgrades are performed within context if(modalityName=="OR"). If modalityName=="NLP" no changes can be made to the effective execution of the codebase.
		/MANUAL; - I have marked all files/functions that require editing with #TODO (in particular GIAANNor_main.py, GIAANNor_datasets.py, GIAANNor_sequenceConcepts.py, GIAANNor_sequenceTokens.py, GIAANNor_globalDefs.py, etc).
		- try not to edit GIAANNcmn_*.py or GIAANNnlp_*.py files unless absolutely necessary; create new GIAANNor_*.py files/functions as necessary.
		/MANUAL; - GIAANNcmn_main.py calls GIAANNor_main.processPrompt()/GIAANNor_main.processDataset(), which executes similar functionality to GIAANNnlp_main.py but for modalityName=="OR".
		- GIAANNor_main.processPrompt() for modalityName=="OR" should use a testset part of the OR dataset as a prompt (rather than an independent prompt file).
		/MANUAL; - I have separated common (GIAANNcmn_*.py), NLP (GIAANNnlp_*.py), and OR (GIAANNor_*.py) code already, however this separation may not be perfect. If you detect any erors in this separation process please correct them (e.g. the presence of common code in nlp files, or the presence of nlp files in common files).
		- ensure to add comments to the code you create using the exact text from the specification for GIAANNproto2a1a.
		- it is recommended to use pytorch or pytorch3D library for GPU accelerated execution of multiple 2D filters in parallel (see above): never execute filters serially.
		/MANUAL; - ensure to modify and use the GIAANNor_main:processSequenceTemplate() code based on GIAANNnlp_main:processSequence() - it does not replicate any print (GIAANNcmn_count) or debug (GIAANNcmn_debug) code so it is easier to understand.
- implement useModalityOR option submodalityName = "image":
	- GIAANNor_datasets.py: add huggingface datasetType for images (find an appropriate dataset for moderate resolution images that has both train and test partitions).
	- use the same GIAANNor_main.py:processSequence() template code as submodalityName=="video" (except for the sequence generation):
	- generate sequence data by augmenting each image:
		- for each image, generate modalityORimageSaccadesPerImage sequences by performing modalityORimageSaccadesPerImage augmentations:
			- saccade augmentations are calculated by translating the image to a random polar coordinates offset from the centre (using modalityORimageSaccadesMaxAngularOffsetDegrees)
			- for each saccade (sequence) generate modalityORimageSnapshotsPerSaccade by taking snapshots along a linear pathway of the saccade offset:
				- crop each augmented snapshot by a predefined amount (dependent on modalityORimageSaccadesMaxAngularOffsetDegrees) so that every snapshot contains only image data (no pixels outside the original image data).
	Implementation notes:
		- ensure the upgrade is performed within context if(submodalityName=="image"). If submodalityName=="video" no changes can be made to the effective execution of the codebase.
- upgrade submodalityName=="image" to perform saccade augmentations between nearby (i.e. adjacent) salient regions of the image: a) segment centres and b) corner features:
	- create GIAANNor_features.py - copy the ATORpt feature detection code that uses the Segment Anything library and OpenCV (https://github.com/bairesearch/ATORpt ATORpt_PTfeatures.py/ATORpt_RFmainSA.py)
- patch submodalityName=="image" to use higher resolution image dataset
- patch numAdjacentFeaturePairsDetected so only adjacent pairs are used for saccades (not all combinations of pairs)
[GPT-5.5:]
- implement modalityORimageSaccadesNumberOfNearbyPairs (for modalityORimageSaccadesUseAdjacentSalientRegions) where this is set to 2 by default - it selects the number of pairs constructed for each feature in the image.
- move image keypoint feature-pair detection and selected-pair-to-saccade-offset conversion code from GIAANNor_datasets.py to GIAANNor_keypoints.py.
- patch all Hugging Face dataset downloads with useLocalDataset=True to keep dataset caches, download caches, assets caches, and direct hub file downloads under datasetFolder.
MANUAL; - update database save paths to only use specialised inference_prompt.txt when useBenchmark=True
- add option modalityORvideoGenerateMultipleSnapshotsPerFrame=True - upgrade submodalityName="video" to use the same modalityORfeatureDetection code as submodalityName="image" to generate multiple snapshots within each video frame for each detected feature (keypoint). The multiple snapshots within each frame should be processed each as a separate subsequence. For each iteration of the video sequence, the nearest keypoints are aligned as pertaining to the same subsequence. Thus the total number of snapshots equals modalityORvideoDuration*modalityORvideoFrameRate/modalityORvideoFramesPerSequenceIteration*numberKeypointsDetectedInFirstSequenceIteration
- add option modalityORvideoGenerateMultipleSnapshotsPerFrameParallel=True - each subsequence is processed in parallel efficiently, each as a separate subsequence. Else, use a python for loop to process each subsequence separately.
- change snapshot extraction method to use modalityORsnapshotFractionOfImage (rather than a fixed pixel dimensions modalityORsnapshotWidth/modalityORsnapshotHeight).
- implement option modalityORsnapshotRetinotopicFieldBias=True - which biases the distribution of cortical column substrate assigned to each snapshot based on a human V1 retinotopic map. Use GIAANNOR-theoreticalReferenceGuide.txt to develop a function for determining the relationship between angular distance from centre of FOV to percentage of columns assigned. Add the table from this guide to the code comments. Note that every snapshot has all columns assigned, but the centre of the FOV has many more columns assigned. It applies to all submodalityName.
- implement option tokensiationMethodOneColumnPerSnapshotPixel=True:
	GIAANNor_sequenceTokens.py: 
		- transform each snapshot such that the total number of pixels in the snapshot = modalityORnumberOfColumns.
		- modify the useModalityOR tokenisation method to assign a token (and respective column) for every pixel in the transformed snapshot. 
		- if modalityORsnapshotRetinotopicFieldBias=True, generate the transformed snapshot by applying a non-linear transform to the image based on the Human V1 reference table from GIAANNOR-theoreticalReferenceGuide.txt (see calculateRetinotopicColumnPercentageForVisualFieldRadiusDegrees). 
	GIAANNor_RFfilters.py:
		- apply the filters on each token (column) pixel and its nearby surrounding pixels.
		- set modalityORnumberOfFeaturesPerColumn = modalityORfilterWidth*modalityORfilterWidth*modalityORfilterChannels
	As per AGENTS.md, ensure that all tokensiationMethodOneColumnPerSnapshotPixel=True code and functions are created within context "if(tokensiationMethodOneColumnPerSnapshotPixel):".
- add option modalityORimageSaccadesEncode=False - do not encode temporal transitions between saccades (only encode co-occuring features like a standard hebbian network).
	- update modalityORimageSnapshotsPerSaccade implementation - if modalityORimageSnapshotsPerSaccade=1: no temporal encoding of saccade movements. if modalityORimageSnapshotsPerSaccade=2: encode start and end of saccade only, if modalityORimageSnapshotsPerSaccade>2: encode start and end of saccade and modalityORimageSnapshotsPerSaccade-2 interpolations between these points.
- change the modalityORimageSaccadesPerImage interpretation to the max number saccades per image (i.e. do not repeat pairs if there are too few pairs in the list).
- modify modalityORsnapshotFractionOfImage implementation so that snapshots taken are always square irrespective of the aspect ratio of the dataset image.
- if modalityORimageSaccadesEncode=False, ensure GIAANN training trains connections between column features if their timeIndex is the same as each other.
- add option modalityORimageSaccadeKeypointsPerEncoding (where it equalled 2 originally before this upgrade) - determines the number of saccade keypoints (transition points) used to encode the context of each selected column feature neuron. Note the total snaphots per column feature neuron encoding = modalityORimageSaccadeKeypointsPerEncoding*modalityORimageSnapshotsPerSaccade+1. Rename modalityORimageSaccadesPerImage to modalityORimageMaxSequencesPerImage.
- change the interpretation of modalityORimageSnapshotsPerSaccade (now expect old value -1):
	if(modalityORimageSaccadesEncode):
		modalityORimageSnapshotsPerSaccade = 1	#default: 1	#if 1: one snapshot per saccade (plus the start point), if >1 add interpolation between saccade keypoints.
	else:
		modalityORimageSnapshotsPerSaccade = 0 #mandatory: 0	#if 0: no temporal encoding of saccade movements
- replace bool option modalityORimageSaccadesEncode with enum (string) option modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="saccades"
- add option modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="distance" - sequence timing (GIAANN segment input encodings) is determined by spatial distance of contextual column feature (in xy column coordinates) away from target column feature in the (retinotopic) visual snapshot map. Use modalityORimageSequenceEncodeDistanceFieldSegments - total number of segments to divide the snapshot visual field into (x or y). The number of encoded segments each individual feature neuron has will depend on its column position in the field (neurons on the edges of the field will have more encoded segments, as their maximum distance from other neurons in the field is higher). For each source neuron of a target neuron (at a relative distance of x, y), calculate its encoded sequence time (i.e. GIAANN segment index) as ceil(sqrt(x^2+y^2)).
- for submodalityName=="video", use option modalityORvideoMaxEncodedSnapshotsPerSequence - which constrains the maximum number of encoded iterations in a sequence of snapshots (i.e. the maximum number of segments of prior context per feature neuron).
- move modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="saccades" and modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="distance" code to new files GIAANNor_sequenceSaccades.py and GIAANNor_sequenceDistance.py
- add option modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="axis" (GIAANNor_sequenceAxis.py), which is derived from modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="distance", but for each axis (X, Y) it effectively encodes sequence inputs based on contextual feature indices independent of their contextual column indices, while the encoding of the other axis remains the same as modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="distance":
	- Conceptual Overview: 
		- for each axis (e.g. X), the target neuron inputs of a particular SANI segment are trained with source neuron feature type input from every column in the retinotopic snapshot map along this axis X (at position y), for every active source neuron feature (and its respective type i.e. index) of the target neuron.
		- the target neuron input timings (segments) are still assigned based on their 2D (x,y) position in the retinotopic snapshot map however, using the same algorithm as modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="distance" (i.e. source column position dependent).
		- this implies that for each trained snapshot, each target neuron segment will be trained with input from columns spanning the entire retinotopic map (along the X and Y axis respectively). However the feature types encoded in each segment (from every column along the axis) will still be dependent on the active source features of that segment.
	- Precise Algorithm:
		- for every target neuron (i.e. active column feature in the retinotopic map) segment, for every source neuron associated with that segment (i.e. active column feature in its corresponding retinotopic map segment), a target segment input is trained for the particular source neuron feature index coming from every column in the retinotopic snapshot map along axis X (and at source column position y).
	- Implementation notes:	
		- the only change from modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="distance" is adding for each axis (X, Y), is adding an effective 1D maxpool operation across all columns of the axis for the feature index of each source neuron (by connecting all features of this type across the axis columns instead of just the source column feature).
- add option modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="axes" (GIAANNor_sequenceAxes.py), which modifies modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="axis" such that for each axis (X, Y) it effectively encodes sequence inputs based on contextual feature indices independent of their contextual column indices, but performs the same operation to both axes.
	- Precise Algorithm:
		- for each axis (e.g. X), for every central target neuron (i.e. central active column feature in the retinotopic map) segment, for every source neuron associated with that segment along the axis X at position y=centre (i.e. active column feature in its corresponding retinotopic map segment), a target segment input is trained for the particular source neuron feature index. The source and target neuron column index information is discarded during training.
	- Implementation notes:	
		- when modalityORimageSequenceEncode=="axes", GIAANNcmn_databaseNetworkTrain effectively only saves connection source feature feature index (not column index) - it does this by setting all trained connection source and target column indices to columnIndex=0.
- upgrade the modalityORimageSequenceEncode = "axes" implementation such that it is completely vectorised.
- update modalityORimageSequenceEncode = "axes" - retain a for loop for each axis (e.g. X).
- patch implementation of modalityORimageSequenceEncode = "axes" - training only occurs for the central target column active features.
- add option modalityORimageSequenceEncodeAxesColumnRandom = True, which trains connection target features to random columns within range 0:modalityORnumberOfColumnsV2 (instead of just modalityORimageSequenceEncodeAxesTargetColumnIndex=0).
- ensure that modalityORfilterChannels, modalityORfiltersPerRotation, and modalityORfiltersRotations are respected in al useModalityOR modes (submodalityName=="video" and "image"). Ie use these constants to define how many RF filters are created and of which orientation and type. ie explicitly creates filters for multiple rotations.
- add option modalityORRFfilterRotationallyInvariant=True, which creates rotationally invariant RF filters. Implementation notes: it does this by linking the output of the equivalent filters at different rotations to modalityORfilterChannelsOutput.
MANUAL; - add option modalityORsnapshotCentreFOVonly

