v2b (Codex IDE GPT-5.5) [under development]:
- add proto GIAANNproto2b1a - start option datasetType=="closedWorldGroundedX" and inferenceReportGroundedAccuracy:
	- due to the whole-word tokenisation of GIAANN, it limits prediction outside of the training-set. However it is not clear the extent to which this limitation is a) preventing hallucination (either false predictions or correct predictions without sufficient grounding within the training-set), or b) not making predictions that are justifiable within the training set (i.e. undergeneralisation).
	- as recommended in the conclusion of GIAANN-grounded-eval-deep-research-report.md, please implement;
		- option datasetType="closedWorldGrounded1": find and implement a closed world train+test dataset that can be used to evaluate the performance of GIAANN modalityName=="NLP" at making grounded predictions (not only correct or incorrect predictions).
		- option inferenceReportGroundedAccuracy=True: new eval code to enable the evaluation of grounded predictions.
- add options datasetType=="closedWorldGrounded2", datasetType=="closedWorldGrounded3", etc. Set inferenceReportGroundedAccuracy=True and closedWorldGroundedDatasetGenerated=False. Note only datasetType=="closedWorldGrounded1" should use closedWorldGroundedDatasetGenerated=True.
- add recommended grounded accuracy class-bias controls and diagnostics:
	- inferenceReportGroundedAccuracyMod1_labelBalancedDataset=True: balance HF-backed closed-world grounded train/eval construction by label and eval pool.
	- inferenceReportGroundedAccuracyMod2_majorityClassBaseline=True: report the grounded accuracy of a majority-label predictor.
	- inferenceReportGroundedAccuracyMod3_perLabelMetrics=True: report target-label counts, predicted-label counts, and per-true-label grounded outcomes.
- keep option inferenceReportGroundedStrongerGroundedNLPmetric=False by default: the claim-derived seed-signature path is retained for comparison but is not the recommended HF-backed grounded eval path.
- upgrade HF-backed grounded datasets to realistic NLP prompts:
	- inferenceReportGroundedRealisticNLPmetric=True: use bounded real claim text in the train/eval sequence rather than id-only verdict templates.
	- grounded eval items store/use a dynamic answer token index, so the answer no longer has to occur at the fixed closedWorldGroundedPromptAnswerTokenIndex position.
	- realistic NLP prompts must remove claim-internal sentence terminators and insert an explicit verdict delimiter so each generated item remains one inference sequence.
MANUAL; - update copyright
MANUAL; - update paper
- add option printTrainSequenceBar=True - print each training sequence iteration using standard tqdm bar
/MANUAL; - add option printEvalSequenceBar=True - print each eval sequence iteration using standard tqdm bar
MANUAL; - set useBenchmarkEvalDataSet=True by default
MANUAL; - extract execution mode useDefault
- update printTrainSequenceText() and buildSequenceWithDelimiters() to use a terminal safe version of token.text - ie certain special characters should not stop the terminal output from being printed. Add a function to convert token.text to a safe text version that will not interfere with terminal printing.

