v2e (Codex IDE GPT-5.5) [under development]:
- add proto GIAANNproto2e1a - start option multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTree:
	- during train if multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTree==False (randomly) assigns an independent branchIndex for all trained neuron segments (see selectFeatureBranchIndex()). [NO CHANGE]
	- during train if multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTree==True derives the branch index of each segment based on the randomly assigned branchIndex:
		- for segmentIndex 0:arrayNumberOfSegments-1(ie for depthIndex multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTreeDepth-1:0):
			- it derives the branch index of the segment by dividing the randomly assigned branchIndex by 2^segmentIndex:
				- note if segmentIndex==0 it will simply use the randomly assigned branch index for the segment (i.e. branchIndex/(2^0) == branchIndex).
				- note if segmentIndex==arrayNumberOfSegments-1 it will simply use branch index 0 for the segment (ie the only branch in the segment at depthIndex==0).
				- note higher segmentIndex (ie lower depthIndex) will have lower branch indices assigned than lower segmentIndex (ie higher depthIndex).
		- if useTrainDuringInference:multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTreeDepthSelectMostActivatedRootBranches:
			- selects the trained the branch index for each target neuron based on the most completely active set of root branches activated by the inference phase.
				- randomly selects a branch index that corresponds to the portion of activated root branches between:
					- multipleDendriticBranchesNumber/(2^numberOfContiguouslyActiveFinalSegments-1)*branchIndex and multipleDendriticBranchesNumber/(2^numberOfContiguouslyActiveFinalSegments-1)*(branchIndex+1); assuming neurons last numberOfContiguouslyActiveFinalSegments were activated during the inference phase, and assuming the last contiguous segment to be activated in the inference phase was on branchIndex.
					- eg if neurons last 3 segments were activated during the inference phase, and the third last segment (ie numberOfContiguouslyActiveFinalSegments==3) to be activated was on branchIndex==3 [of possible values 0->3] then assuming multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTreeDepth==arrayNumberOfSegments==7:
						 - the randomly assigned branch index to be trained for the neuron must be between multipleDendriticBranchesNumber/(2^(3-1))*3 and multipleDendriticBranchesNumber/(2^(3-1)*(3+1)
			- multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTreeDepthSelectMostActivatedRootBranches assumes that enforceSequentialActivation==False was set during the inference phase of useTrainDuringInference:
				- ie segment activation was not sequentially dependent (higher segment indices at lower branch depths could be activated without lower segment indices at higher branch depths first being activated).
				- eg inferenceSegmentTiming=="biased" or inferenceSegmentTiming = "none" was selected during the inference phase of useTrainDuringInference (either of these options will disable enforceSequentialActivation).
		- initalises multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTreeDepth = numSeedTokensInference (ie arrayNumberOfSegments) - depth of the dendritic binary tree.
		- initalises multipleDendriticBranchesNumber = 2^(multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTreeDepth-1).
		- assumes multipleDendriticBranchesRandom==True.
	- during inference if multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTree==True:
		- update the enforceSequentialActivation==True logic to reflect the binary tree connectivity:
			- if multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTree==True then segment activations must be filtered based on their prior segment branch indices in the binary tree.
		- update the neuron activation logic (segment summation) to reflect the binary tree connectivity:
			- if multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTree==False segment activations are summed first (independently across branches). [NO CHANGE]
			- if multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTree==True segment activations are summed based on their prior segment branch indices in the binary tree.
		- update any other inference code that is required to reflect the binary tree connectivity (ensure to report on what has been changed). 
	MANUAL; - rename numberOfDendriticBranches/randomlyAssignBranches to multipleDendriticBranchesNumber/multipleDendriticBranchesRandom.
	Implementation Notes:
		- implementation must use vectorised pytorch code (no python for loops across branches, python for loops only across segments where necessary).
		- do not change any existing code in the codebase unrelated to specific multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTree==True behaviour.
		- ensure to encapsulate all multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTree==True specific behaviour within context if(multipleDendriticBranchesBinaryTree) as per AGENTS.md.

