	- patch exact-time SANI segment gating so missing previous-segment time entries are no longer treated as time 0; candidate segment activation now requires the previous segment to have an explicit stored time and currentTime - previousTime == 1 in both standard and binary-tree paths.
	- add option enforceSequentialActivationFeatureSegmentsOnly (default: True, orig: True) - ensures that sequential enforcement (either enforceAllSegmentsMustBeActive or enforceLastSegmentMustBeActive) only checks that feature segments have a previous feature segment active (column segments are ignore in sequential enforcement).
	- add option enforceAllSegmentsMustBeActiveFeatureSegmentsOnly (default: True, rig: False) - ensures that enforceAllSegmentsMustBeActive (regardless of the value of enforceSequentialActivation) only checks that all feature segments are active, not column segments.
	- update algorithmMatrixSANIenforceRequirement="enforceAllSegmentsMustBeActive"+enforceAllSegmentsMustBeActiveFeatureSegmentsOnly=False: never check the activation value of the last concept segment (as this corresponds to the current/internal column in the sequence and may be inactive if the prediction target is an initial feature in this column).
	- update enforceSequentialActivationFeatureSegmentsOnly=False: never enforce the activation value of the last concept segment (as this corresponds to the current/internal column in the sequence and may be inactive if the prediction target is an initial feature in this column).
MANUAL; - if(executionMode=="train"): re-enable defaults useGPUdense=False+useGPUsparse=False.
MANUAL; - if(executionMode=="train"): optionally set storeDatabaseFeatureConnectionsAndColumnFeatureNeuronsInRam = True (non-default optimisation: only possible for training of low database sizes <= ~1M training sequences).
MANUAL; - update paper

